      "content": "a \"routine audit\" sounds a bit cleaner, yeah. but even then, if we say an audit \"identified\" it, people might ask why the audit didn't catch the misconfiguration before it was exposed for three days. basically, if we say it was an audit, we're still technically hiding the fact that it was an accidental exposure. \n\nis there a way to frame it so we don't even have to mention the bucket or the exposure at all? like, just make it sound like a standard system update or something so people don't even think there was a security risk to begin with?",
